%% Call graph for the UDS SecurityAccess path on the synthetic TC1766 lab firmware.
%% Shows the complete call chain from CAN reception to hardware reset,
%% with the functions that were rewritten for the lab binary highlighted.

flowchart TD
    EXT["Tester sends UDS SecurityAccess request over CAN"]
    EXT --> RX["CAN message object receive"]
    RX --> CHK["CAN channel receive check"]
    CHK --> POLL["Diagnostic poll task"]
    POLL --> GATE["UDS gatekeeper<br/>Validates session and routes by service ID"]
    GATE --> TBL["Main dispatch table<br/>20 entries, one per supported service ID"]
    TBL -->|Service 0x27| DISP["SecurityAccess dispatcher<br/>Routes by sub-function parity"]
    DISP -->|RequestSeed or SendKey| S2K["Seed-to-key primitive<br/>Bit-reversed Fibonacci LFSR"]
    DISP -->|Special sub-functions| ALT["Alternative handler<br/>ECU-specific variants"]
    DISP --> VAL["Anti-tamper validator<br/>Always tail-called after every request"]
    VAL -->|Integrity check fails| RST["Hardware reset trigger<br/>Captures crash log and resets ECU"]
    RST --> DEAD["ECU resets — session ends"]
    S2K --> DISP
    ALT --> DISP

    classDef rewrite fill:#fff3bf,stroke:#806a00,color:#1c1700
    classDef hwreset fill:#ffd3d3,stroke:#7a0000,color:#1c0000
    class DISP,S2K rewrite
    class RST hwreset
